  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "After his parents died, the boy was made his uncle's ward.",
      "cn": "双亲去世后, 小男孩由其叔叔监护."
    },
    {
      "en": "Alex was made a ward of court.",
      "cn": "亚历克斯由法院监护。"
    },
    {
      "en": "As soon as we found this out, we closed the ward.",
      "cn": "我们一发现此事就关闭了病房。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Ask to speak to the sister on the ward.",
      "cn": "请求和病房里的护士长说话。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Have a drop. It'll ward off the cold of the night.",
      "cn": "喝一口挡挡夜里的寒气."
    },
    {
      "en": "He is in the surgical ward.",
      "cn": "他住在外科病房."
    },
    {
      "en": "He landed in a psychiatric ward.",
      "cn": "他被关进了精神病房。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He managed to free one hand to ward off a punch.",
      "cn": "他设法挣脱出一只手来挡住了一拳。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He passed through the doorway into Ward B.",
      "cn": "他穿过门口进入B病房。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Many people swear by vitamin C's ability to ward off colds.",
      "cn": "许多人深信维生素C能预防感冒。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr Ward wasn't a rogue at all.",
      "cn": "沃德先生根本不是恶棍。"
    },
    {
      "en": "she put up a hand as if to ward him off.",
      "cn": "她举起一只手，好像要将他挡开。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Such a thin padded coat cannot ward off the cold mountain wind.",
      "cn": "这么薄的棉衣在高山上挡不住寒风."
    },
    {
      "en": "The hospital has a medical ward and a surgical ward.",
      "cn": "这家医院有内科病房和外科病房."
    },
    {
      "en": "the other patients in the ward",
      "cn": "病房里的其他病人"
    },
    {
      "en": "The ward of the hospital is in the charge of Dr. Green.",
      "cn": "医院的这间病房由格林医生负责."
    },
    {
      "en": "This ward is in [ under ] the charge of Dr Green.",
